  "texts": [
    "That said, what counts as harmful or inappropriate depends on the cultural context; for example, there are cultural biases against different groups in different societal conditions, different cultural or religious taboos exist, and different types of criminal activities are more prevalent in different countries.",
    "It is also known that a foreign language itself can be an attack vector [13], in that models are more vulnerable to malicious attacks in languages other than English.",
    "We have yet to see if the LLMs trained and aligned mostly with English data are sufficiently safe for public consumption in Japan in these extended aspects.AnswerCarefully(AC)foot_1 is a dataset for improving the safety of Japanese LLM output, developed with the above background in mind.",
    "Figure 1 is an example AC data.",
    "While there are existing datasets such as JBBQ [16], TruthfulQA [7] and JSocialFact [9] that target the safety of Japanese LLM, they are restricted to specific domains: JBBQ focuses solely on bias and prejudice, and TruthfulQA and JSocialFact deal with factuality only."
  ],
